===Etymology===
si+inu([[死]]+[[往ぬ]])

===Verb===
{{ja-verb|type=1|tr=intrans|しぬ}}
# to [[die]]
# to [[become]] [[lifeless]], to [[lack]] [[vitality]], to be [[loss]] of [[vigor]]

====Conjugation====
{{ja-go-nu|死|し|shi}}

====Synonyms====
* [[死]]する (shi suru) {{qualifier|honorific}}
* [[亡くなる]] (nakunaru) {{qualifier|polite}}
* [[崩御|崩御する]] (hougyo-suru) {{qualifier|most honorific}} king, queen, emperor, empress
* [[身罷る]] (mimakaru) {{qualifier|classic}}, {{qualifier|more honorific}}
* [[去ぬ]] (inu) {{qualifier|classic}}
* [[くたばる]] (kutabaru) {{qualifier|vulgar}}
* [[タヒる]] (tahiru) {{qualifier|slang}}, {{qualifier|net jargon}}

===Trivia===
The only modern Japanese verb which ends in [[ぬ]] (an older example is {{term|去ぬ||to go, to leave|tr=いぬ, inu|lang=ja}}, which is now archaic). Accordingly, it is used in textbooks to illustrate conjugation of such verbs, despite its morbid subject.

